        {
          "obj_id": "S1",
          "kind": "setup",
          "label": "Setup S-1",
          "nl": "design-based finite-population potential-outcome system on n=2m units: the only randomness is a sign assignment law P (a PMF on the finite space {-1,1}^n); potential outcomes Y_i(z) and the GATE estimand tau are fixed finite-population objects — FiniteDesign Ω is exactly a PMF (p, p_nonneg, p_sum) over a finite assignment space with finite-sum E/Var/Cov; instantiate Ω := (Fin n -> Sign) i.e. {-1,1}^n so P : FiniteDesign Ω. Sign-symmetry / block-exchangeability (P_m^bal, P_m^sym) are predicates ON such a design (built by BalancedDesignClass / blockExchangeableDesignClass nodes). Y_i(z):(Ω)->Fin n->R and tau=n^{-1} sum (Y_i(1_n)-Y_i(-1_n)) are plain ambient functions (no dedicated Causalean PO structure; lean_local_search PotentialOutcome -> none, only Panel.Exposure exists) and are motivational: no proved statement references them, so they are trivial Mathlib functions carried in this world.",
          "lean": null,
          "status": "unreviewed",
          "sorry_free": false
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "S2",
          "kind": "setup",
          "label": "Setup S-2",
          "nl": "real n x n symmetric-matrix / Euclidean objective-geometry world (Mathlib): traces, PSD cone, Frobenius (Schatten-2) norm, the balanced two-block spectral decomposition, and the two-parameter block-symmetric slice X(u,v) with its reduced triangle T_m — Built over Mathlib matrices: Matrix.trace, Matrix.PosSemidef, the Frobenius norm, EuclideanSpace/inner products and the spectral theorem for symmetric matrices supply every primitive. L_m^dagger (Moore-Penrose pseudoinverse) is only ever consumed through its eigenvalues (1/(a+b),1/(2b),0) via lem:block-spectral-coordinates, so it is realized by its spectral action, not a general pseudoinverse theory. bypass-justified: the Causalean analogue for the ambient probability layer (FiniteDesign, S1) is at the design-law abstraction, whereas E_m^blk/F/Delta are purely algebraic over R^{n x n}; lean_local_search {elliptope, assignmentCovariance, Laplacian, Frobenius} returned none, so this world is a Mathlib-matrix bypass. The derived scalar frontiers (kappa_cut, r_cut, kappa_iid, r_gap^{+-}, r_star) are R-valued closed forms living in this world; r_star has no statement node (honest open scope) and is bound here only as a symbol.",
          "lean": null,
          "status": "unreviewed",
          "sorry_free": false
        }
      ]
