        {
          "obj_id": "lem:frobenius-center-certificate",
          "kind": "lemma",
          "label": "Lemma L-5",
          "nl": "On T_m, the point (1,1,1) is the unique minimizer of sqrt(qx^2+y^2+z^2). It is a minimizer of c_x x+c_y y+c_z z+kappa sqrt(qx^2+y^2+z^2) for finite kappa only if c_x/q=c_y=c_z; under this equality and kappa>0 it is the unique minimizer.",
