        },
        {
          "obj_id": "lem:pm-reduced-slice-characterization",
          "kind": "lemma",
          "label": "Lemma L-6",
          "nl": "After full two-block symmetrization, the plus-minus-one covariance image in spectral coordinates is T_m when m is even and is T_m intersect {y+z>=2/m} when m is odd. In particular, for odd m the spread vertex (m/(m-1),0,0) is not implementable, while for even m every point of E_m^blk is implementable.",
          "lean": {
            "file": "Helpers/ParitySlice.lean",
            "decl": "pm_reduced_slice_characterization",
            "decl_kind": "lemma",
            "line": 0
          },
          "status": "matched",
          "sorry_free": true
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "lem:weighted-simplex-active-set",
          "kind": "lemma",
          "label": "Lemma L-7",
          "nl": "Let I={x,y,z}, M=2m, beta_x=1/q, beta_y=beta_z=1, and alpha=(alpha_x,alpha_y,alpha_z). On Delta_M={t_i>=0: sum_i t_i=M}, minimize Phi(t)=sum_i alpha_i t_i+kappa sqrt(sum_i beta_i t_i^2). If kappa>0, the minimizer is unique and is obtained by the following active-set formula. For each nonempty S subset I set A_S=sum_{i in S} beta_i^{-1}, mu_S=A_S^{-1} sum_{i in S} alpha_i beta_i^{-1}, and V_S=sum_{i in S}(alpha_i-mu_S)^2 beta_i^{-1}. If lambda_S=mu_S+sqrt((kappa^2-V_S)/A_S) is real, lambda_S>max_{i in S} alpha_i, and alpha_j>=lambda_S for every j notin S, then t_i=M((lambda_S-alpha_i)/beta_i)/sum_{h in S}((lambda_S-alpha_h)/beta_h) for i in S and t_j=0 for j notin S. Exactly one S satisfies these conditions, and the displayed point is the unique minimizer with value M lambda_S. Singleton S gives a vertex, two-point S gives an edge minimizer, and S=I gives the interior minimizer. If kappa=0, the minimizer set is the exposed face conv{M e_i: alpha_i=min_j alpha_j}; a closed-form selector may be chosen from that face without changing the value.",
          "lean": {
            "file": "Helpers/SimplexActiveSet.lean",
            "decl": "weighted_simplex_active_set",
            "decl_kind": "lemma",
            "line": 0
          },
          "status": "matched",
          "sorry_free": true
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "lem:weighted-simplex-truncation",
          "kind": "lemma",
          "label": "Lemma L-8",
          "nl": "In the notation of lem:weighted-simplex-active-set, let K_d={t in Delta_M: t_y+t_z>=d} with 0<=d<=M. Use the kappa=0 tie convention that the relaxed selector is chosen in K_d when the relaxed argmin face meets K_d. If the selected relaxed minimizer t_rel belongs to K_d, it is also a minimizer over K_d. If t_rel is not in K_d, then every constrained optimum may be chosen on the segment H_d={t_x=M-d, t_y=s, t_z=d-s, 0<=s<=d}. On H_d the objective is g_d(s)=alpha_x(M-d)+alpha_z d+(alpha_y-alpha_z)s+kappa sqrt((M-d)^2/q+s^2+(d-s)^2). For kappa>0, writing A_d=(M-d)^2/q and delta=alpha_y-alpha_z, the minimizer is s=0 if delta>=kappa d/sqrt(A_d+d^2), s=d if delta<=-kappa d/sqrt(A_d+d^2), and otherwise s=(d-delta sqrt((A_d+d^2/2)/(kappa^2-delta^2/2)))/2. For kappa=0, any endpoint minimizing the linear function is selected: s=0 if delta>=0 and s=d if delta<=0.",
          "lean": {
            "file": "Helpers/SimplexTruncation.lean",
            "decl": "weighted_simplex_truncation",
            "decl_kind": "lemma",
            "line": 0
          },
          "status": "matched",
          "sorry_free": true
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "lem:rounding-gap-reduction",
          "kind": "lemma",
          "label": "Lemma L-9",
          "nl": "Let q=2(m-1), T_m={x,y,z>=0: qx+y+z=2m}, phi_{r,kappa}(x,y,z)=c_x x+c_y y+c_z z+kappa sqrt(qx^2+y^2+z^2), and d_m=0 if m is even and d_m=2/m if m is odd. Then Delta_m^pm(r,kappa)=min_{(x,y,z) in T_m, y+z>=d_m} phi_{r,kappa}(x,y,z)-min_{(x,y,z) in T_m} phi_{r,kappa}(x,y,z).",
          "lean": {
