    {
      "kind": "theorem",
      "items": [
        {
          "obj_id": "thm:cut-corner-exactness",
          "kind": "theorem",
          "label": "Theorem T-1",
          "nl": "Assume ass:two-block-homophily. Set r_cut(m,a,b,kappa)=min{2b(a+b)(1-kappa/(a-b)), 2b(2m-2b-kappa)}. If 0<=r<r_cut(m,a,b,kappa), then X_cut is the unique minimizer of F_{r,kappa} over E_m^blk. Hence Delta_m^pm(r,kappa)=0, X_cut is the unique minimizer over C_m^pm, and P_cut attains that implementable optimum. (The range 0<=r<r_cut(m,a,b,kappa) is nonempty exactly when 0<=kappa<min{a-b,2(m-b)}, which in particular requires b<m; this is a non-vacuity remark, not a hypothesis.) At the boundary r=r_cut uniqueness can fail already when kappa=0, so the theorem uses the strict inequality r<r_cut.",
          "lean": {
            "file": "Tcut.lean",
            "decl": "cut_corner_exactness",
            "decl_kind": "theorem",
            "line": 0
          },
          "status": "matched",
          "sorry_free": true
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "thm:robust-corner-exactness",
          "kind": "theorem",
          "label": "Theorem T-2",
          "nl": "Assume ass:two-block-homophily. Finite-kappa iid exactness holds only on the affine-balanced locus. More precisely, I_n is a minimizer of F_{r,kappa} over E_m^blk for some finite kappa if and only if a+3b=2m and r=2b(a+b), equivalently r=4b(m-b). On this locus, for every kappa>0, I_n is the unique relaxed minimizer and the implementable optimum is attained by P_iid, with P_iid in P_m^sym by def:block-exchangeable-design-class and X(P_iid)=I_n. Off this locus, I_n is not a minimizer for any finite kappa, although minimizers converge to I_n as kappa tends to infinity.",
          "lean": {
            "file": "Trobust.lean",
            "decl": "robust_corner_exactness",
            "decl_kind": "theorem",
            "line": 0
          },
          "status": "matched",
          "sorry_free": true
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "thm:gap-window",
          "kind": "theorem",
          "label": "Theorem T-3",
          "nl": "Assume ass:two-block-homophily, ass:low-scale-two-block, and ass:odd-community-size. With q=2(m-1), define kappa_gap(m,a,b):=((2m-a-3b)(a-b)sqrt(q))/(a+b) and r_cut_gap(m,a,b,kappa):=2b(a+b)(1-kappa/(a-b)). Define R_x^-(m,a,b,kappa)=2b(a+b)(1+kappa/((a-b)sqrt(q))) and R_x^+(m,a,b,kappa)=(a+b)(2m-a-b-kappa/sqrt(q)). Define r_gap^-(m,a,b,kappa)=(R_x^-(m,a,b,kappa)+R_x^+(m,a,b,kappa))/2 and r_gap^+(m,a,b,kappa)=R_x^+(m,a,b,kappa). Then for every 0 <= kappa < kappa_gap(m,a,b), r_cut_gap(m,a,b,kappa) < r_gap^-(m,a,b,kappa) < r_gap^+(m,a,b,kappa), and for every r in (r_gap^-,r_gap^+) the spread vertex X_spread in E_m^blk with spectral coordinates (m/(m-1),0,0) is the unique relaxed minimizer but is not plus-minus-one implementable. Consequently Delta_m^pm(r,kappa)>0 throughout that interval. The oddness restriction is necessary: if m is even, the whole block elliptope slice is implementable and the claimed positive gap is false.",
          "lean": {
            "file": "Tgap.lean",
            "decl": "gap_window",
            "decl_kind": "theorem",
            "line": 0
          },
          "status": "matched",
          "sorry_free": true
        },
        {
          "obj_id": "thm:sharp-rho-star",
          "kind": "theorem",
          "label": "Theorem T-4",
          "nl": "Under ass:two-block-homophily, with r,kappa in [0,infty), the theorem asserts EXACTLY the following conjunction (mirroring the Lean statement): (i) rho_star(m,a,b,r,kappa) = Delta_m^pm(r,kappa); (ii) 0 <= rho_star and 0 <= Delta_m^pm (definitional domain [0,infty)); (iii) rho_star=0 iff there is a relaxed minimizer over T_m (a point of T_m minimizing the reduced objective) with y+z >= d_m; (iv) for kappa>0 the relaxed minimizer over T_m is UNIQUE, and rho_star=0 iff that unique minimizer satisfies y+z >= d_m; (v) for kappa=0 a point of T_m is a relaxed minimizer iff it lies on the exposed face of the alpha=(c_x/q,c_y,c_z)-minimizing coordinates; (vi) for even m (d_m=0) rho_star=0 throughout; (vii) ACTIVE-SET COMPUTATION (lem:weighted-simplex-active-set): for kappa>0 the unique relaxed minimizer is the active-set point of an admissible support/multiplier (S,lambda) under the change of variables t=(qx,y,z) (alpha=sharpAlpha, beta=sharpBeta), and the relaxed value equals 2m*lambda; (viii) TRUNCATION CORRECTION (lem:weighted-simplex-truncation): when the relaxed argmin set is disjoint from {y+z >= d_m}, the implementable value is attained on the truncation segment {y+z=d_m} at the endpoint/interior selector truncSelector. No r_star frontier/boundary is asserted (honest open scope).",
